      "span_text": "It is important to note that the pauses induced by the collector do not happen frequently. If pauses of 2ms occurred once every 3ms, then pause times would loose their meaning and we should look at mutator's minimum utilization (MMU). However, in our case, the pauses form a negligible part of the collection cycle, and are split far apart from each other. [CITATION_1] , and the first published implementation was by Ungar [CITATION_2] ."
